spec: agent-core.ai-docs/v1
namespace: "Domain\\Event\\Lifecycle"
fqcn: "Ineersa\\AgentCore\\Domain\\Event\\Lifecycle"
updatedAt: 2026-04-19
description: Typed lifecycle event subclasses extending AbstractLifecycleRunEvent. Each maps to a CoreLifecycleEventType constant.
files[11]{file,type,summary}:
  MessageStartEvent.php,readonly final class,Represents a domain event signaling the initiation of a message processing lifecycle within the agent core. This immutable value object encapsulates the context required to track the start of asynchronous or synchronous message handling operations.
  AbstractLifecycleRunEvent.php,readonly abstract class,"Represents an immutable event capturing the state of a lifecycle run within the agent core domain. It encapsulates essential metadata such as run identification, sequence numbering, and turn context to ensure event integrity."
  AgentStartEvent.php,readonly final class,Represents a domain event signaling the initiation of an agent's lifecycle. This immutable value object captures the context required to track when and where an agent begins execution. It serves as a durable record for event sourcing and audit trails.
  ToolExecutionEndEvent.php,readonly final class,A value object representing the completion of a tool execution within an agent's lifecycle. It encapsulates the result data and metadata required to transition the agent state after a tool call finishes. This event serves as a immutable record for downstream processing or logging.
  TurnStartEvent.php,readonly final class,Represents a domain event signaling the commencement of a new turn within an agent's lifecycle. This immutable value object encapsulates the timestamp and context required to coordinate turn-based processing.
  AgentEndEvent.php,readonly final class,Represents a domain event signaling the termination of an agent's lifecycle. This immutable value object captures the context required to process agent completion within the event-driven architecture.
  ToolExecutionStartEvent.php,readonly final class,A value object representing the start of a tool execution within an agent's lifecycle. It captures the context required to track when a specific tool begins processing a request. This event serves as a marker for timing and state transitions in the agent's execution flow.
  TurnEndEvent.php,readonly final class,A value object representing the conclusion of a single turn within an agent's lifecycle. It encapsulates immutable data regarding the turn's outcome and context to facilitate event-driven state transitions.
  ToolExecutionUpdateEvent.php,readonly final class,Represents a domain event signaling an update to the execution state of a tool within an agent's lifecycle. This immutable value object captures the context required to track tool execution progress without modifying system state directly.
  MessageEndEvent.php,readonly final class,Represents a domain event signaling the completion of a message processing lifecycle within an agent system. This immutable value object encapsulates the context required to track and react to message termination events.
  MessageUpdateEvent.php,readonly final class,Represents a domain event triggered when a message within an agent's lifecycle is updated. This immutable value object encapsulates the context of the change to facilitate event-driven architecture patterns.